a¬–Z<?php exit; ?>a:6:{s:10:"last_error";s:0:"";s:10:"last_query";s:69:"SELECT wpw6_posts.* FROM wpw6_posts WHERE ID IN (1344,1332,1173,1157)";s:11:"last_result";a:4:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1157";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2018-01-21 23:21:17";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2018-01-21 17:36:17";s:12:"post_content";s:6486:"<p style="text-align: justify;">There are very few people who are ‚Äúpredestined‚Äù to be an actor and she is definitely one of them, we are talking about this stunning Aussie born actress- <strong><em>Sarah Snook</em></strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><em>Sarah Snook</em></strong> was born on 28 July 1987 in Adelaide, South Australia. She studied in Blair at St John‚Äôs Grammar School and due to her acting skills she got a scholarship at Scotch College, Mitcham. After completing her high school, she went to National Institute of Dramatic Arts (NIDA) and graduated in 2008.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Career </strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">When Sarah was at NIDA, she performed in some stage productions like <strong><em>Macbeth</em></strong> and <strong><em>Gallipoli.</em></strong> She was then associated with the <strong><em>State Theatre Company of South Australia</em></strong> and acted in <strong><em>King Lear</em></strong>. Recently, in 2016 she made her West End debut from Ibsen‚Äôs play <strong><em>The Master Builder</em></strong> at the Old Mic Theatre in London.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Snook is a big television star as well; she has acted in a number of TV series such as <strong><em>All Saints</em></strong>, <strong><em>Sisters of War</em></strong>, <strong><em>Packed to the Rafters</em></strong>, <strong><em>Spirited</em></strong>, <strong><em>The Secret River</em></strong>, <strong><em>The Beautiful Lie</em></strong> and <strong><em>The Black Mirror</em></strong><em>, </em>which is a recent Netflix series. Among them, she was much loved in the series <strong><em>Sisters of War</em></strong> (2010) and <strong><em>Sleeping Beauty</em></strong> (2011) which got 6.5/10 and 5.3/10 from IMDb respectively.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1160" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/predestination-lg-300x187.jpg" alt="" width="556" height="346" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">In 2010, Sarah started acting in short films like <strong><em>Crystal Jam</em></strong> and <strong><em>The Best Man</em></strong>. Subsequently, in 2011, she landed one of the important roles of her career as Stevie in the movie <strong><em>Not Suitable for Children</em></strong>. Her performance in the movie was widely praised and was adorned with awards as well.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Sarah then acted on one of the most successful science fiction thriller films <strong><em>Predestination</em></strong>, based on the short story by Robert A. Heinlein ‚ÄúAll you Zombies‚Äù. She portrayed the role of Jane/John in the movie, an androgynous character who struggles with her transformation from female to the male body. She has played the role brilliantly; also her sheer dedication to bringing justice to the role is highly commendable ergo she was acclaimed universally.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Furthermore, Snook was featured in films such as <strong><em>These Final Hours</em></strong> (2013), <strong><em>Jessabelle </em></strong>(2014), <strong><em>The Dressmaker</em></strong> (2015) another critically appraised movie alongside Kate Winslet, <strong><em>Oddball</em></strong> (2015), <strong><em>Holding the Man</em></strong> (2015), <strong><em>Steve Jobs</em></strong> (2015) as well as <strong><em>The Glass Castle</em></strong> (2017).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Upcoming projects</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Sarah will be seen in Australian-American supernatural horror movie <strong><em>Winchester</em></strong> which is being directed by Michael and Peter Spierig to be released in February 2018. Additionally, she is busy shooting for¬†<strong><em>Sibling Rivalry</em></strong> and <strong><em>The Second Coming</em></strong>. She is also set to star in HBO American TV drama series <strong><em>Succession</em></strong>, created by Jesse Armstrong. The series will comprise 10 episodes and its air date is yet to be declared.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1162" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/succession-hbo-3-585x400-300x183.jpeg" alt="" width="537" height="327" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Personal Life</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Sarah is a very private person.¬† She lives in Australia. Though she is active in social media like Twitter and Instagram, not much is known about her love life or her marital status.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Achievements</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Sarah Snook is an extremely talented actor; she has been nominated for many awards and also has won a few. She has won <strong><em>Australian Academy for Cinema and Television Awards (AACTA)</em></strong> of <strong><em>Best Lead Actress in a Television drama </em></strong>for <strong><em>Sisters of War</em></strong> in 2012. She also received <strong><em>Best Lead Actress Award</em></strong> for <strong><em>Not Suitable for Children</em></strong> from <strong><em>AACTA</em></strong> in 2013. Sarah was honored with her third <strong><em>AACTA </em></strong>awards of <strong><em>Best Lead Actress</em></strong> for her role in <strong><em>Predestination </em></strong>in 2014. Moreover, in 2015 she got an <strong><em>Australian Film Critics Association (AFCA)</em></strong> award of <strong><em>Best Supporting Actress</em></strong> for <strong><em>These final hours</em></strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1161" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Sarah-Snook-300x207.jpg" alt="" width="547" height="377" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Net Worth</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Snook has given remarkable performances in movies, television and the theatre. The net worth of Snook is reported to be $1 million.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Sarah Snook has made her name in the theatre, television and also movies with her hard work and devotion. She is a delight to watch who knows exactly what is to be done in order to do justice to any character she portrays; we wish that this driven actress will continue to make us spellbound with her awesome performance in the forthcoming days.</p>
&nbsp;

